-- Brazil Posts March Current Account Gap of $3.3 Billion
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2012-04-24T14:19:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/brazil-posts-march-current-account-gap-of-3-3-billion-correct-.html
(Corrects month to March in headline and text.)  Brazil  posted a $3.3 billion
current account deficit in March, the central bank said today in
a report released in Brasilia. Analysts had expected a deficit
of $4 billion, according to the median forecast in a Bloomberg
survey of 19 economists.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Harry Maurer at 
